main event: An unidentified object was observed in Gainesville, Florida on April 2, 1966, by three witnesses.
interesting points: The object appeared to travel at a fast rate of speed and emitted red and white lights., It changed course at a right angle and then descended vertically before disappearing., There was insufficient data for complete evaluation of the sighting., The witnesses included military and civilian individuals who were deemed reliable and credible., The report was followed up with requests for more information from the Air Force.
